annotationA: Vang-like protein; Van Gogh (Vang) is a four-pass transmembrane protein that localizes to cell junctions. It is part of the Frizzled-dependent planar polarity pathway that establishes planar polarity in epithelia. Vang is also implicated in nervous system patterning
annotationB: Myosin-2 essential light chain; Protein binding; calcium ion binding; myosin binding; myosin heavy chain binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: actin filament-based movement
